3. Accordingly, the PSI for Senegal shall be amended as follows:   
a. In paragraph 1(d) of the PSI for Senegal, “June 30, 2010” shall be replaced by “May 28, 2010”;   
b. A new paragraph 1(e) shall be added to read as follows:

The monthly balance sheet of the Central Bank, with a maximum lag of one month;   
The consolidated balance sheet of banks with a maximum lag of two months; The monetary survey, on a quarterly basis, with a maximum lag of two months;   
The lending and deposit interest rates of commercial banks, on a monthly basis; and   
Prudential supervision and financial soundness indicators for bank financial institutions, as reported in the Table entitled Situation des Etablissements de Crédit vis- $\grave{a}$ -vis du Dispositif Prudentiel (Survey of Credit Institutions in Relation to the Prudential Framework), on a quarterly basis.
